  <p class="sec-body" id="weatherNote" style="margin-bottom:0">Jharkhand has three seasons: hot summer (March–June), monsoon (July–September) and a beautiful cool winter (October–February). October to March is ideal — the Chota Nagpur forests glow in golden light, waterfalls run full from monsoon, the Sarhul and Karma festivals fill villages with flowers and drums and wildlife is most easily spotted.</p>
